Romance for Bugle (Czech: Romance pro kdlovku) is a 1967 Czechoslovakian drama film directed by Otakar Vvra. It was entered into the 5th Moscow International Film Festival where it won the Special Silver Prize. It is based on the same name lyrical epic poem written in 1961 by Frantiek Hrubn.

